restmbmaster
------------------------------------------
restmbmaster is a simple daemon that allows user to access Modbus slaves over
Rest API. The slaves could be either connected over serial line (Modbus RTU
protocol), or over TCP (Modbus TCP protocol).

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libmicrohttpd12-0.9.71-1bl1
  libmodbus5-3.1.6-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jpirko/restmbmaster

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jpirko/restmbmaster/archive/v3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack restmbmaster-3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./restmbmaster-3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/restmbmaster-3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/restmbmaster-3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(restmbmaster)
  /usr/bin/restmbmaster.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/restmbmaster.README
  /usr/share/doc/restmbmaster/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/restmbmaster/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man5/restmbmaster.conf.5.gz
  /usr/share/man/man8/restmbmaster.8.gz

